  "prompt": "How do I get printouts of past IRCTC journey tickets?",
  "response": "To get printouts of past IRCTC journey tickets, you can follow these steps:\n\n1. **Visit the IRCTC Website**: Go to the official IRCTC website at [www.irctc.co.in](https://www.irctc.co.in).\n\n2. **Login to Your Account**: Click on the \"Login\" button on the top right corner of the homepage and enter your credentials (user ID and password).\n\n3. **Navigate to 'My Account'**: Once logged in, go to the \"My Account\" section.\n\n4. **Access 'Booking History'**: Look for a link or option that says \"Booking History\" or \"My Bookings.\" This will display a list of your past journey tickets.\n\n5. **Select the Ticket**: Find the ticket for which you want to get a printout. You may see options like 'Print' or 'View Details' alongside each ticket.\n\n6. **Print the Ticket**: Click on the 'Print' option associated with the specific booking. This will typically open the ticket in a printable format. You can then print it directly from your browser.\n\n7. **Download (Optional)**: If you want to save a digital copy, you might also have the option to download the ticket as a PDF before printing it.\n\n8. **Mobile App**: If you prefer using a mobile device, you can also retrieve your booking history through the IRCTC mobile app. Log in, go to \"My Bookings,\" and follow similar steps to print the ticket.\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to get printouts of your past IRCTC journey tickets easily. If you encounter any issues, consider contacting IRCTC customer support for further assistance.",
